<DocsLayout title="Implementation" description="How the implementation phase works: direct Claude through tickets, verify each one, and ship.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Implementation</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You've read the requirements, design spec, and architecture. Now you implement. This phase is where you direct Claude Code through every ticket in the backlog, one at a time, until the project is done.</p>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Every ticket follows the same loop: <strong class="text-text">direct → verify → review → merge</strong>. You tell Claude to start a ticket. Claude implements it, commits, and opens a PR. You verify the result against the acceptance criteria. You read the reviews. You merge or ask for fixes. Then you move to the next ticket.</p>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Work through these sections in order:</p>

